Edward - I know very little of any American Indian tribe culture or language and I refuse to make believe that I do. By doing so, to me, dishonors that culture and peoples. I see it as another form of cultural rape that I want no part of, so excuse me if I don't talk the talk on this particular thread. I truely hate phonies with a passion and I must set that example for my daughter.<br><br>
But, saying that, I have followed and studied your writings and have concluded that a lot of what you speak parallels the concept of bushido, of which I am more familiar with. This similarity suprises me none.<br><br>
Part of Bushido deals with &quot;honoring your enemy&quot;, in this case, Spatz. Frankly, the earlier exchanges with Spatz and others left me cold and was totally tiresome. Nothing was accomplished, no ground was gained. Hamburger Hill and Khe Sahn were battles won but days later abandoned to the enemy. No ground gained. Sharp words and rhetoric wins immediate battles but in the end, no ground is gained. Wasted expenditures.<br><br>
Your recent course change truely is that of a warrior, a samarai. If you lost any brothers along your path, of which I really doubt, you have gain this one. You have nothing to grieve.<br><br>
So, to you, Mon Capitan, I salute you. For your reluctance to engage in the &quot;gook&quot; garbage, I salute you. Continue with the real battles and keep ignoring the diversionary tactics.
